      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. its hard to want to \"just be here\" when there is nothing to look forward to. like, everyone talks about \"hope\" and \"resilience\" but that feels so fake. it's like being told to enjoy a house that's actively burning down. i feel like i'm just waiting for the inevitable. does it even make sense to keep fighting for a world that’s already gone?",
